- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed framework involves the use of sequence-to-sequence networks and optimization techniques, which are commonly used in AI research. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper utilizes an ensemble of sequence-to-sequence networks, which is a common technique in neural network research. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper applies the proposed framework to renewable energy sources, which involves control and optimization of energy systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper introduces a new resampling technique and modifies the framework for automated feature selection, which are relevant to software engineering research.
